  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="page" n="120">
        <pb n="120"/>
        <ab xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/1272,471,2023,699/max/0/default.jpg">
          קַבָּלַת פָּנִים<lb/>
        KABBALAT PANIM WELCOMING
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_B" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/2866,1829,1223,941/max/0/default.jpg">
          בָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ<lb/>
        אֱלֹהֵינוּ, מֶלֶךְ הָעוֹלָם,<lb/>
        אֲשֶׁר קִדְּשָׁנוּ בְּמִצְוֹתָיו,<lb/>
        וְצִוָּנוּ לְהַדְלִיק<lb/>
        נֵר שֶׁל שַׁבָּת.
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_C" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/406,1871,1087,908/max/0/default.jpg">
          BARUCH atah, Adonai<lb/>
        Eloheinu, Melech haolam,<lb/>
        asher kid&apos;shanu b&apos;mitzvotav,<lb/>
        v&apos;tzivanu l&apos;hadlik<lb/>
        ner shel Shabbat.
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_D" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/874,2830,2840,527/max/0/default.jpg">
          BLESSED ARE YOU, Adonai our God, Sovereign of the universe,<lb/>
        who hallows us with mitzvot,<lb/>
        commanding us to kindle the light of Shabbat.
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="block_E" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F6c4bac16-639d-4efb-80fc-190ead3118e5.jp2/455,5674,3687,594/max/0/default.jpg">
          Shabbat Candle Blessing - The mitzvah of kindling Shabbat lights in the home is an early rabbinic<lb/>
        practice (M. Shabbat 2:1ff.) The Shabbat candle blessing is first recorded in the ninth-century<lb/>
        prayerbook, Seder Rav Amram. Lighting Shabbat candles as part of the synagogue service is an<lb/>
        innovation of Reform Judaism.
        </ab>
      </div>
